# Keep the build context tiny so `COPY . .` and the context upload are fast.
# Anything that is a build output, a downloaded dependency, VCS metadata, or docs
# is regenerated in-image (or simply unneeded) and must not enter the context.
#
# NOTE: `migrations/` is intentionally NOT ignored — services/api/Dockerfile's
# runtime stage does `COPY migrations ./migrations`, and the JS Dockerfiles need
# the per-package package.json manifests, so source dirs stay in the context.

# --- Rust build output (rebuilt via cargo-chef + BuildKit cache mounts) ---
target
**/target

# --- Node / Bun deps + framework output (reinstalled / rebuilt in-image) ---
node_modules
**/node_modules
.next
**/.next
.turbo
**/.turbo
dist
**/dist
*.tsbuildinfo
**/*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts
**/next-env.d.ts

# --- VCS / CI / local tooling (never needed to build an image) ---
.git
.gitignore
.github
.dockerignore

# --- Env / secrets: passed at runtime, never baked into an image layer ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- Docs / licenses / editor / OS cruft (not referenced by any build) ---
*.md
LICENSE
.DS_Store
*.log
.vscode
.idea

# --- Compose files are not part of any image build context ---
compose.yaml
compose.prod.yaml
